content.beginner:
Passing props through many levels of components is called **prop drilling** — it's annoying. Context lets you share data without passing props at every level:

```jsx
const ThemeContext = createContext('light');

// Wrap your tree
<ThemeContext.Provider value="dark">
  <App />
</ThemeContext.Provider>

// Use it anywhere inside
const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);

`useMemo` caches a computed value so it isn't recalculated every render:

```jsx
const expensiveResult = useMemo(() => {
  return heavyComputation(data);
}, [data]); // only recalculates when data changes
```

`useCallback` does the same but for functions.

Controlled inputs keep form state in React:

```jsx
function Form() {
  const [name, setName] = useState('');

  return (
    <form onSubmit={e => { e.preventDefault(); alert(name); }}>
      <input
        value={name}
        onChange={e => setName(e.target.value)}
      />
      <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
  );
}
